  	  	<p>Protecting your private information is our priority. This Statement of Privacy applies to http://www.ldsareabook.org (the &ldquo;Site&rdquo;) and LDS Area Book and governs data collection and usage. For the purposes of this Privacy Policy, unless otherwise noted, all references to LDS Area Book include the Site and LDSAB. The LDSAB website is a communication and collaboration site. By using the LDSAB website, you consent to the data practices described in this statement.</p><p><strong>Collection of your Personal Information</strong></p><p>LDSAB may collect personally identifiable information, such as your name and email address.</p><p>Information about your computer hardware and software may be automatically collected by LDSAB. This information can include: your IP address, browser type, domain names, access times and referring website addresses. This information is used for the operation of the service, to maintain quality of the service, and to provide general statistics regarding use of the LDSAB website.</p><p>LDSAB encourages you to review the privacy statements of websites you choose to link to from LDSAB so that you can understand how those websites collect, use and share your information. LDSAB is not responsible for the privacy statements or other content on websites outside of the LDSAB website.</p><p><strong>Use of your Personal Information</strong></p>LDSAB collects and uses your personal information to operate its website(s) and deliver the services you have requested.</p><p>LDSAB may also use your personally identifiable information to inform you of other products or services available from LDSAB and its affiliates. LDSAB may also contact you via surveys to conduct research about your opinion of current services or of potential new services that may be offered.</p><p>LDSAB does not sell, rent or lease its customer lists to third parties. LDSAB will disclose your personal information, without notice, only if required to do so by law or in the good faith belief that such action is necessary to: (a) conform to the edicts of the law or comply with legal process served on LDSAB or the Site; (b) protect and defend the rights or property of LDSAB; and, (c) act under exigent circumstances to protect the personal safety of users of LDSAB, or the public.</p><p>If you create an area book or become an administrator of any area book, you agree to disclose your name and email address in connection with your area book so that other users may contact you through the Site or through your displayed email address in order to request access to your area book.</p><p><strong>Use of Cookies</strong></p><p>The LDSAB website may use &ldquo;cookies&rdquo; to help you personalize your online experience. A cookie is a text file that is placed on your hard disk by a web page server. Cookies cannot be used to run programs or deliver viruses to your computer. Cookies are uniquely assigned to you, and can only be read by a web server in the domain that issued the cookie to you.</p><p>One of the primary purposes of cookies is to provide a convenience feature to save you time. The purpose of a cookie is to tell the Web server that you have returned to a specific page. For example, if you personalize LDSAB pages, or register with LDSAB site or services, a cookie helps LDSAB to recall your specific information on subsequent visits. This simplifies the process of recording your information. When you return to the same LDSAB website, the information you previously provided can be retrieved, so you can easily use the LDSAB features that you customized. This includes cookies to retrieve your area book information.</p><p>You have the ability to accept or decline cookies. Most Web browsers automatically accept cookies, but you can usually modify your browser setting to decline cookies if you prefer. If you choose to decline cookies, you will not be able to experience the interactive features of the LDSAB services or websites you visit.</p><p><strong>Security of your Personal Information</strong></p><p>To secure your personal information from unauthorized access, use or disclosure, LDSAB uses the following:</p><p>Server database encryption with a user-set password that is not accessible or recoverable to server administrators. This allows you to confidently upload information regarding your area, individuals, and families knowing that your information is not accessible to anyone, including LDSAB, unless you share your ward password with those individuals or administrators.</p><p>Additionally, when personal information is transmitted it is protected through the use of encryption, such as the Secure Sockets Layer (SSL) protocol.</p><p><strong>Children Under Thirteen</strong></p><p>LDSAB does not knowingly collect personally identifiable information from children under the age of thirteen. If you are under the age of thirteen, you must ask your parent or guardian for permission to use this website.</p><p><strong>Opt-Out & Unsubscribe</strong></p><p>We respect your privacy and give you an opportunity to opt-out of receiving announcements of certain information. Users may opt-out of receiving any or all communications from LDSAB by contacting us here:</p><p>Email: support@ldsareabook.org</p><p><strong>Changes to this Statement</strong></p><p>LDSAB will occasionally update this Statement of Privacy to reflect company and customer feedback. LDSAB encourages you to periodically review this Statement to be informed of how LDSAB is protecting your information.</p><p><strong>Contact Information</strong></p><p>LDSAB welcomes your questions or comments regarding this Statement of Privacy. If you believe that LDSAB has not adhered to this Statement, please contact LDSAB at:</p><p>LDS Area  Book Email Address: support@ldsareabook.org</p><p>Effective as of August 10, 2013</p>
